race.comment: PETITE PALACE (10) won a 58 here heavily bet before the spell and she looked a run short resuming 35 days ago in a CL5 at the Gold Coast. She's trialled strongly since and will race forward from an inside gate. Suited. Ditto JACKA STANDS ALONE (5) who likely had excuses at the Sunshine Coast last time. He led and won this grade by a big space at Toowoomba prior and has been freshened. Has a handy gate and is sure to give a big sight. SNITZOND (11) is third-up and is an improved galloper. He led and was overrun in the latter stages at Ipswich off the Toowoomba win and will be better for it. Will likely control the race and take catching. MEDALS (3) turned his form around winning this grade at Toowoomba. Has to run out the longer sprint today and that's a niggle.
